1 WHEREAS, the I-12 and I-55 interchange in Tangipahoa Parish presents ongoing
2 safety concerns due to heavy commercial freight traffic, complex merging patterns, and
3 recurring congestion, which have resulted in serious collisions, overturned freight trucks, and
4 traffic shutdowns; and
5 WHEREAS, common improvements to interstates typically involve widening
6 projects, interchange reconstruction, asphalt overlays, concrete median protection, and
7 bridge replacements.
8 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
9 urge and request the Department of Transportation and Development to implement
10 improvements to I-12 in the parish of Livingston.
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
12 secretary of the Department of Transportation and Development.
